I am a fan of Pret, but this branch doesn’t deserve the brand. This review is based on a full week eating 3 meals a day. 1. The bathrooms are NEVER clean, not once, in fact they were always GROSS and our of toilet paper. 2. The staff could not be more grumpy. It feels like you are asking for free food. 3. Out of condiments for 2 days! 4. Closed before hours without updating google maps - so if you go late you’ll waste the trip 5. Pret’s philosophy says that they don’t sell you food from the day before, but that’s not the case here. 6. You can’t see the price you are being billed and they don’t offer the receipt. They need new management, training and to hire people who are down to do the job.

I love this Pret store. I visit New York twice a year and come back every time. The staff are friendly and accommodating always. I especially like the fact that they have decaf and regular coffee that is self serve so that I can make a custom cup of coffee. A few times the decaf was out and the manager went to the back and made fresh decaf and brought it out to me with no charge:)
The employees are really nice the environment is really nice a good place for breakfast launch

More training is needed here. I asked for a toasted bagel with cream cheese. There was no cream cheese, so I asked for butter.  I sit down and find I have a room temperature bagel and ice cold butter.  Of course, the butter should be cold. I go back to the cashier, and she says we don't toast, it's warm. It was NOT. And why didn't she say so when I ordered? I asked how can I spread cold butter on it, to which she just shrugged her shoulders. Really? And there were no knives in the utensil kiosk, though she insisted there were.  I checked twice. When she finally said they would get some, I just said never mind, I'm leaving. If my americano were not exceptional, I would have given one star.
The coffee is good and the baristas are the nicest baristas I've ever encountered.

This place is awesome. I cant speak much for the menu, only been here once but its seems alright. The staff is very nice, they gave us food for free because they had left overs I guess and they gave us water with ice and cookies. Great place to study and hangout with friends. Definitely coming here again!
Very friendly and helpful staff. Love the chicken parm hot wrap and the honey banana bowl. Highly recommend

Flat bread was way too hard.  Per Carlos whom I assume was the manager, that's the way it's supposed to be.  Funny how after I peeled about 20% of the hard crust off, the rest of the flat bread was noticeably softer, what one would expect from a flat bread sandwich.

I always like Pret as they give a lot of reward perks and in this case, the cashier gave me a free drink (Latte) on the house.  All in all, good hot food selections, excellent wraps but i would shy away from the cold sanwiches (that they can heat for you) as they are hard to chew or bite into for that matter.

I have been there a few times around 6pm weekdays. Staff is always friendly but I think they might have management issues.  Coffee offerings are mesy. Both times I ordered they forgot about it and I had to ask for it again a few minutes later.  The counter behind the registers always look very messy and disorganized which inevitably make. Me wonder - if public facing areas look like that, imagine what their kitchen must look like.

Just like the rest of the franchise, this Pret has good organic food, prepared daily, ready to go along with fair trade coffee. Occasionally, they have challenges here: if you can guess the coffee, you get a cup free. Also, if they catch you waiting for a while they may give something away on the house. They're very customer-focused. Great place to eat.

Good, healthy food at affordable prices. Quality coffee. Staff are always friendly too which is surprising given how busy/hectic it gets.

Very nice place! Pret A Manger is an English chain that is based in London. Pretty sells sandwiches, soups, salads, and Pastry's. People come to this location mostly for the Sandwiches, and coffee ☕️.  The staff are mostly young, cheerful people. The people that come here are mostly young students (which adds 1 star.) This Pret A Manger is a good size, you will probably find a seat. The sandwiches are very good! Why do I go to Pret all the time? Because it reminds me of how good London is.

I like the idea of serving fresh quality food and trying to be sustainable. My complain is that the cashier charged me a different more expensive juice than the one I bought. First I thought she did it because I am not a regular there and I had a strong foreign accent. Then I realized that they often make mistakes in  the bills so be careful. Sometimes it may be that the price tag is wrong or the cashiers are overloaded that they charge the wrong items and that may even be in your favor.
